                                <div class="card-body">
                                 <p>To register as a customer for the water district payment system and view your billing online, please follow the steps below:</p>

<ol>
	<li>
	<p>Visit the official website of your water district. You can usually find this information on your water bill or by doing a quick online search.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Look for the &quot;Customer Registration&quot; or &quot;Sign Up&quot; option on the website&#39;s homepage or navigation menu.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Click on the registration link, which will typically take you to a registration form.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Fill out the required information in the registration form accurately. This usually includes details such as your name, address, contact number, email address, and customer account number (if applicable). Make sure to provide all the necessary information as requested.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Create a username and password for your online account. Choose a strong password that includes a combination of letters, numbers, and special characters to ensure the security of your account.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Once you have completed the registration form, review the provided information to ensure accuracy. Then, submit the form.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>After successfully registering, you will receive a confirmation email or message with instructions on how to activate your account. Follow the instructions provided to activate your account.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Once your account is activated, you can log in to the water district&#39;s website using your username and password.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>After logging in, navigate to the &quot;Billing&quot; or &quot;My Account&quot; section to view your billing details. Here, you should be able to see your current and past bills, payment history, and other relevant information.</p>
	</li>
</ol>

<p>Now, let&#39;s proceed to the access guide for making payments via GCash or credit card:</p>

<p>Payment via GCash:</p>

<ol>
	<li>
	<p>Ensure that you have a registered GCash account and have sufficient funds in your GCash wallet.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Log in to your water district&#39;s online payment system using the registration credentials you set up earlier.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Navigate to the &quot;Payment&quot; or &quot;Pay Bill&quot; section on the website.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Select the option for GCash as your payment method.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Enter your GCash mobile number and the amount you wish to pay. Verify the details and confirm the transaction.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>You will receive a notification on your registered GCash mobile number to authorize the payment. Follow the instructions in the notification to complete the payment.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Once the payment is successful, you should receive a confirmation message or email from the water district.</p>
	</li>
</ol>

<p>Payment via Credit Card:</p>

<ol>
	<li>
	<p>Log in to your water district&#39;s online payment system using your registration credentials.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Navigate to the &quot;Payment&quot; or &quot;Pay Bill&quot; section on the website.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Select the option for credit card payment.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Enter your credit card details, including the card number, expiration date, CVV code, and billing address.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Verify the entered information and confirm the payment amount.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Submit the payment request. The website will process the transaction and communicate with your credit card provider for authorization.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>If the payment is authorized, you will receive a confirmation message or email regarding the successful transaction.</p>
	</li>
</ol>

<p>Remember to keep records of your payment confirmation for future reference. If you encounter any issues during the registration process or while making payments, it&#39;s best to contact your water district&#39;s customer support for further assistance.</p>

